'''''Gondomania''''', also known in Japan as {{nihongo|'''''Makyō Senshi'''''|魔境戦士|''Demon Warrior''}}, is a  1987 [[Shoot 'em up|scrolling shooter]] [[arcade video game]] initially released in Japan by [[Data East]].

== Plot ==
The Gondos, a race of [[Extraterrestrial life|alien]] beings, [[Alien abduction|steals]] your significant other and takes them to the [[planet]] of [[Thorns, spines, and prickles|thorns]].<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|title=Gondomania – Hardcore Gaming 101|url=http://www.hardcoregaming101.net/gondomania/|access-date=2021-10-08|language=en-US}}</ref> The premise of game is to take down the Gondos though various levels and [[Boss (video games)|boss fights]]. It takes place in a futuristic medieval world and includes [[dragon]]s and [[soldier]]s.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Gondomania - Videogame by Nihon Bussan/AV Japan|url=https://www.arcade-museum.com/game_detail.php?game_id=7981|access-date=2021-10-08|website=www.arcade-museum.com}}</ref>

== Gameplay ==
The game was designed for play on a classic arcade console. One button activates the guns, while the other button throws a type of sub-weapon and the [[joystick]] allows the player to move in various directions.<ref name="auto"/> A rotary joystick allows the player to aim and fire sub-weapons in eight different directions.<ref name="auto"/> Similar to other scrolling shooters, ''Gondomania'' allows players to progress through ten levels. Enemies in ''Gondomania'' drop coins when they are defeated, which allows a player to purchase [[power-up]]s.<ref name="auto"/> This differs from typical scrolling shooters in that it requires an additional layer of strategy to decide which item to purchase and when as opposed to the typical scrolling shooter where the player receives pre-programmed power-ups.<ref>{{Cite web|title=[꿀딴지곰 겜덕연구소] 오락실에서 스틱을 '빙글빙글' 돌리던 게임들! 기억나세요?|url=https://game.donga.com/89851/|access-date=2021-11-03|website=game.donga.com|date=21 July 2018 |language=ko}}</ref>

